<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1546,2041]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1935" box="[151,277,1546,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Somatiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Somatiidae</taxonomicName>
is a small family of seven morphologically similar Neotropical species in the single genus 
<emphasis box="[1282,1380,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[1282,1377,1547,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Somatiidae" genus="Somatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Somatia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
with only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1805" box="[208,314,1583,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Tephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestiva">
<emphasis box="[208,314,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">S. aestiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F.) encountered with relative frequency. The genus was first keyed and then catalogued by 
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="255 - 257" refId="ref96499" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1968 c) The genus Somatia Schiner, II. (Diptera: Somatiidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 70, 255 - 257." type="journal article" year="1968">
Steyskal (1968 
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[219,232,1618,1644]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="2" refId="ref96536" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1970 a) 94. Family Somatiidae In: Papavero, N., (Ed.), A Catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas South of the United States. Departamento de Zoologia, Secretaria da Agricultura, Sao Paulo, pp. 2." type="book chapter" year="1970">c</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1970a), and later reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lonsdale, O. &amp; McAlpine, D. K." box="[584,920,1618,1644]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="833 - 835" refId="ref86491" refString="Lonsdale, O. &amp; McAlpine, D. K. (2010) 59: Somatiidae. In: Brown, B. V., Borkent, A., Cumming, J. M., Woodley, N. E. &amp; Zum- bado, M. A. (Eds.), Manual of Central American Diptera. Vol. 2. NRC Research Press, Ottawa, pp. 833 - 835." type="book chapter" year="2010">Lonsdale &amp; McAlpine (2010)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1546,2041]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1653,1680]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Biology.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." box="[304,488,1654,1681]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref87390" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2006) Insects: Their natural history and diversity: With a photographic guide to insects of eastern North America. Firefly Books Ltd., Richmond Hill, ntario, 736 pp." type="book" year="2006">Marshall (2006)</bibRefCitation>
first observed adult 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[727,819,1655,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Somatiidae" genus="Somatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[727,819,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Somatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feeding on a dead caterpillar. Species have also been observed at the extrafloral nectaries of several plants. 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho-Filho, F. S." box="[770,1025,1690,1716]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="54 - 56" refId="ref77658" refString="Carvalho-Filho, F. S. (2017) Aggregation of Somatia aestiva (Fabricius) (Diptera: Somatiidae) on leaves of Solanum stramonifolium Jacq. EntomoBrasilis, 10 (1), 54 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.12741 / ebrasilis. v 10 i 1.657" type="journal article" year="2017">Carvalho-Filho (2017)</bibRefCitation>
found numerous specimens feeding on the underside of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[372,711,1726,1753]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stramonifolium">
<emphasis box="[372,647,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Solanum stramonifolium</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[725,854,1726,1753]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Solanaceae</taxonomicName>
) leaves, as well as one specimen “licking the calyx” of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kunth) Miers" authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1863" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" box="[184,635,1762,1789]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pleonotoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jasminifolia">
<emphasis box="[184,463,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pleonotoma jasminifolia</emphasis>
(Kunth) Miers
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[652,811,1762,1789]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bignoniaceae</taxonomicName>
). The author speculated that extra-floral nectaries may explain the presence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[413,505,1799,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Somatiidae" genus="Somatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[413,505,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Somatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens on other plants mentioned in the literature, including legumes (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref87553" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2012) Flies: The Natural History and Diversity of Diptera. Firefly Books Ltd., Richmond Hill, Ontario, 616 pp." type="book" year="2012">Marshall, 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hespenheide, H. A." box="[232,459,1833,1860]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="191 - 204" refId="ref83638" refString="Hespenheide, H. A. (1985) Insect visitors to extrafloral nectaries of Byttneria aculeata (Sterculiacea): relative importance of roles. Ecological Entomology, 10, 191 - 204. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1985. tb 00548. x" type="journal article" year="1985">Hespenheide (1985)</bibRefCitation>
also noted that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[641,733,1835,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Somatiidae" genus="Somatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[641,733,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Somatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“are common visitors at extrafloral nectaries of other plants”, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D. A." box="[199,382,1870,1897]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref82095" refString="Grimaldi, D. A. (2016) Familia Somatiidae. Available from: http: // www. inbio. ac. cr / papers / insectoscr / Texto 125. html (accessed 14 August 2017)" type="url" year="2016">Grimaldi (2016)</bibRefCitation>
found 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[461,553,1871,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Somatiidae" genus="Somatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[461,553,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Somatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at nectaries of 
<taxonomicName box="[723,838,1870,1896]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[723,838,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Passiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[853,1020,1870,1897]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Passifloraceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1546,2041]" box="[199,531,1906,1932]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,1906,1932]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Immature stages.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
